<HEADLINE> 120,000 Mozambicans Need Relief Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- About 10,000 tons of relief
food is needed for the 120,000 Mozambicans from now to the
harvest season in April 1999, according to a press release from
World Food Program which was made public here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 120,000 people plagued by drought and flood in the
country, 65,000 need emergent food aid, the World Food Program
release said.
</P>
<P>
Some of the disaster-stricken Mozambicans might have to sell
off their means of production, such as their farming cattle, the
release said, adding that there is luckily no report of death
yet.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that 19 hungry people in the country have died
for eating unhealthy food, the news release said.
</P>
<P>
The World Food Program is trying to aid the country with food,
and the Mozambican government is to send drinking water and food
to the disaster-ridden area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
