<DOCNO> XIE19980927.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwandan President Visits Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Rwandan President Pasteur
Bizimungu made a short working visit to Uganda Saturday during
which he held closed-door talks with President Yoweri Museveni.
</P>
<P>
Hope Kevegere, press secretary to President Museveni, told
Xinhua Saturday evening that the talks focused on bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
However, she did not reveal whether they also talked about the
deepening crisis in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
The talks were held in President Museveni's home at Rwakitura
in southwestern district of Mbarara, she added.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda and Uganda have been accused by DRC President Laurent
Kabila of fomenting and backing the rebellion which erupted in
DRC's capital Kinshasa on August 2 and spread quickly to other
parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Both Rwanda and Uganda denied the charge. Rwanda said it did
not send troops to back the Tutsi rebels in DRC while Uganda
admitted its military presence in the central African country but
it said the troops there are safeguarding the national security
of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
With the deepening of the crisis, more African countries began
to side with President Kabila, leaving Rwanda and Uganda a bit
lonely.  
</P>
</TEXT>
