<HEADLINE> Engine Problem Forces Sabena Flight to Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Engine problems forced a
Sabena flight to an emergency landing not long after takeoff on
Saturday but no one was injured in the incident.
</P>
<P>
The Lisbon-bound Boeing 737 had to discharge most of its fuel
before making the emergency landing. The 104 passengers and crew
aboard were immediately evacuated from the plane that was then
towed to the garage for close inspection.
</P>
<P>
Some parts in one of the air plane's two engines came off and
fell on the ground. Some pieces even fell on parked cars and
broke the back and side windows of a Mercedes-Benz.
</P>
<P>
The fallen pieces measured some 20 to 30 centimeters in length.
</P>
<P>
The airport authorities are investigating the damage in the
engine and the cause that inflicted the damage but declined to say
more about the incident.
Sabena is the national carrier of Belgium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
