<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-26 18:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Denies Persecution of Afghan Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 26 (Xinhua) -- An Iranian official here
on Saturday dismissed the claims as "pure fabrication" that
Afghan refugees were being persecuted in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the official news agency IRNA, deputy director
general of the foreign nationals and expatriates department at
the Interior Ministry Abdulreza Haji Arab denied the recent
claim of the Afghan Taliban militia on the safety of Afghan
refugees living in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Haji Arab said that no move has been made against Afghan
refugees so far which could be inconsistent with the
international conventions.
</P>
<P>
The crime of the Afghan Taliban militia in killing Iranian
diplomats and journalist have not had any negative impact on
the safety of Afghan refugees residing in Iran, he said.
</P>
<P>
Haji Arab said that the Iranian government and nation treat
Afghan refugees based on Islamic principles and international
conventions and would spare no efforts to support the oppressed
Muslim nation of Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) representative
offices in Tehran and several other provinces are supervising
all affairs concerning refugees, he added.
</P>
<P>
However, an Iranian newspaper reported on Tuesday that some
Iranians took advantage of the present circumstances between
Iran and the Taliban clashed with Afghan refugees in Iran.
</P>
<P>
A group of 40 Iranians clashed with Afghan refugees in
Isfahan province on September 11 and injured some of them, an
official from the province was quoted by Iran Daily as saying.
</P>
<P>
The clash came one day after the Taliban confirmed the
killing of nine Iranian diplomats and reporter in northern
Afghanistan, which angered the Iranian nation.
</P>
<P>
Iranian leaders and authorities pledged to take revenge on
the Taliban for the killing, but the Iranian government is
making efforts to solve the issue through diplomatic channels.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
