<HEADLINE> Tanzania, Mozambique to Have Cross-border Vessel Services  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The
Tanzania-Mozambique Friendship Association (TAMOFA) will by the
the border of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
TAMOFA sources said on Saturday in Dar es Salaam that this is
a first step to alleviate transport problems for people living in
Mtwara in south Tanzania and Pemba in north Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
TAMOFA and a sister association of Mozambique, COMATA, are
working together to promote trade links between the two
countries, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A vessel, owned by a private company of Mozambique, will go
into service after authorities go through formalities for the
service. The boat is able to carry 60 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the sources said TAMOFA and COMATA have chartered a
privately owned plane flying from Pemba to Mtwara in order to
promote tourism and trade. The weekly flight has attracted a lot
of passengers.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs and
International Co-operation, Emmanuel Mwambulukutu, appealed on
Thursday at the tenth anniversary of the TAMOFA that the two
countries should enhance bilateral cooperation, especially trade
links. 
</P>
