<HEADLINE> China Routs Indonesia 5-0 in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANJI, Northeast China, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Yu and
Zheng Yu wrapped up China's 5-0 victory over Indonesia here on
Sunday after winning the reverse singles of a Davis Cup
Asia/Oceania Zone Group One relegation playoff.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, a 23-year-old strong baseliner, rallied from one set
down to beat Indonesia's Andrian Raturandang 3-6, 6-3, 6-4 while
Zheng rolled over Feby Widiyanto 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
The two dead rubbers were played in the best-of-three format
as China had taken an unbeatable 3-0 lead on Saturday after Zheng
teamed up with Li Si to win the doubles against Bonit Wiryawan
and Sulistyo Wibowo 4-6, 7=6 (9-7), 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the opening singles Friday, Zhang battled four hours before
overcoming Widiyanto 6-1, 6-2, 4-6, 1-6, 7-5, and Zheng surprised
Raturandang with a 6-3, 6-2, 6-2 win.
</P>
<P>
The victory means that China keeps its place in the group.
</P>
<P>
With the retirement of former top two veterans Pan Bing and
Xia Jiaping at the end of last year, China has to rely on the two
relatively inexperienced youngsters. 
</P>
