<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Emphasizes All-Round Rural Reform (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Referring to the deepening of rural reform, Jiang
pointed out that a long-term management mechanism based on the
household contract and land contract systems must be maintained.
</P>
<P>
The central government has now adopted a very clear land
contract policy which will prolong the contract period for another
30 years, and it may not be necessary to change the policy even
then, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang outlined the target of deepening rural economic reform
based on household contract management, and supported by the
agricultural socialization service, the marketing system for
agricultural products, and the government's support and protection
of agriculture, and it must also comply with the development of
socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Expanding grass-roots level democracy in rural areas and
guaranteeing democratic rights of the farmers are the most
extensive practices of socialist democracy in rural areas, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
At present, the government must work toward the direct election
of village committees, open discussion among the villagers and
making the village affairs known among the village members, he
said, noting the the expansion of democracy in rural areas must
adhere to the leadership of the Party and must be carried out in
accordance with law, and in orderly arrangement.
</P>
<P>
As for the long-term development of agriculture, Jiang cited
water, and science and technology as two important areas. He also
urged governments at each level to take practical steps to build
agricultural infrastructural facilities and adhere to the
guideline of invigorating agriculture through science and
education.
</P>
<P>
In this way, agricultural growth can be brought on the track of
relying on scientific and technological progress, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
