<DOCNO> XIE19980927.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Emphasizes All-Round Rural Reform (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here on Friday that Party committees and governments at all
levels must give priority to agriculture development and continue
to push ahead with rural reform in accordance with the socialist
market economy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, conducted an inspection tour in east China's
Anhui Province from September 21 to 26, and delivered an important
speech in Hefei, capital of Anhui, on September 25.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the experience of China's rural reform over the past
two decades, Jiang noted that a new framework, in line with the
socialist market economy, has basically come into being in the
rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Overall agricultural-production capacity has greatly increased,
and farmers' living standards have improved remarkably, he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the success of China's rural reform is a
great victory of Deng Xiaoping Theory, and the course of rural
reform demonstrates that only Deng Xiaoping Theory can free China
from the restraint of old concepts and a rigid system, and carry
out the building of socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Without Deng Xiaoping Theory, China would not have a complete
set of basic policies on the Party's rural work at present, and
would not have today's huge achievements, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that gaining the farmers' enthusiasm is the primary
starting point in drawing up rural policies.
</P>
<P>
Government at each level must audaciously explore
effective ways of realizing public ownership in rural areas,
improving the structure of the rural ownership system, and stick to
the market orientation of rural reform, Jiang said, noting
that these are basic experience of rural reform and must be
firmly followed up.
</P>
</TEXT>
