<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First County Relocation in Three Gorges Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The relocation of Zigui
County, hometown of China's great ancient poet Qu Yuan, has been
completed to make way for the construction of the gigantic Three
Gorges Dam.
</P>
<P>
The relocation program will replace 100,000 residents, and the
entire county will be relocated to Maoping town, one kilometer
away from the Three Gorges Project on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Zigui County is the first place to complete replacement among
the 11 towns in the Three Gorges Dam area to be relocated before
they are submerged when the project is completed early next
century.
</P>
<P>
The State Council approved the relocation of Zigui County in
June 1991. Construction of the new county, which is 37 kilometers
from the old one, began in 1993.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 390 million yuan (47 million
U.S. dollars), infrastructural facilities including
transportation, electricity, and post and telecommunications
networks have been installed in the new county over the past six
years.
</P>
<P>
By early September, some 180 governmental institutions had
moved to the new site and 18,600 residents had begun their new
life in new homes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
