<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Training Aircraft Crash in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed Sunday
in an aircraft crash at Postogola, about 10 kilometers northeast
of here, the national BSS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The training aircraft of Air Parabat, a private airlines,
crashed on the western bank of the Buriganga at about 10:25 a.m.
local time, killing both the pilot and the copilot.
</P>
<P>
The Cessana-150 aircraft was returning to Dhaka from Barisal,
some 120 kilometers south of the capital, and sent an SOS signal
at 10:22, the BSS said.
</P>
<P>
An air force rescue helicopter was sent to search for the
ill-fated aircraft and found it burning, with both pilots trapped
inside, it added.
</P>
<P>
It was not known what had caused the accident. 
</P>
