<HEADLINE> Israeli District Court Sentences Friend of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Tel Aviv District Court
sentenced Margalit Har Shefi to nine months in prison Sunday
morning for failing to prevent the assassination of former
Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin.
</P>
<P>
Har Shefi, a close girl friend of convicted assassin Yigal Amir,
also received a suspended sentence of 15 months.
</P>
<P>
Rabin was assassinated by Amir at a peace rally in Tel Aviv in
November 1995.
</P>
<P>
The judge said that if Har Shefi had shown more responsibility
and taken a more vigorous action, it would be possible that the
murder might not have occurred.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors have asked a maximum penalty of two years, arguing
that Har Shefi knew two previous attempts by Amir to kill Rabin.
</P>
<P>
But 22-year-old Har Shefi claimed that she was innocent and
said she would appeal the sentence.
</P>
<P>
Har Shefi was convicted in June of failing to prevent the
crime. And she would begin her prison term on October 27 if her
appeal was rejected.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Labor party welcomed the sentence, saying in a
statement that it is important three years after Rabin's
assassination to see the justice has been done for the
perpetrators, accomplices and those who failed to prevent the
crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
