Saturday passed an 80 billion U.S. dollar tax cut package and sent
it onto rough sailing in the Senate. President Bill Clinton
promised to veto it, repeating the Democratic criticism that the
measure is paid for by dipping into the budget surplus generated
by Social Security funds.
</P>
<P>
-- Residents from Pensacola, Florida, to New Orleans, Luisiana,
fortified their homes and moved farther inland as forecasters
predicted that Hurricane Georges could hit shores as early as
Sunday morning. The storm, which killed more than 260 people in
the Caribbean, had struck southern Florida Saturday before
entering the Gulf of Mexico. 
