<HEADLINE> Kenyans Monopolize World Half Marathon Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan runners monopolized
the world half marathon titles when Paul Koech took the men's
event while Tegla Loroupe won the women's crown at the world
championships in Uster, Switzerland, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Koech covered the 21.1 kilometers in one hour and one second,
23 seconds ahead of Hendrick Ramaala of South Africa in the
second place and Khalid Skah of Morocco in the third place, both
of whom had a timing of 1:00:24.
</P>
<P>
Loroupe successfully defended her world title, registering a
time of one hour eight minutes and 29 seconds.
</P>
<P>
South African Elana Meyer finished three seconds behind to
grab the silver medal while Lidia Simon of Romania won the bronze
in 1:08.58. 
</P>
