</P>
<P>
Har Shefi, close friend of convicted assassin Yigal Amir, also
received a suspended sentence of 15 months.
</P>
<P>
Rabin was assassinated by Amir at a peace rally in Tel Aviv in
November 1995.
</P>
<P>
The judge said that if Har Shefi has shown more responsibility
and taken a more vigorous action, it was possible that the murder
might not have occurred.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors have asked a maximum penalty of two years, arguing
that Har Shefi knew two previous attempts by Amir to kill Rabin.
</P>
<P>
But 22-year-old Har Shefi claimed that he was innocent and
said he would appeal the sentence.
</P>
<P>
Har Shefi was convicted of failing to prevent the crime in
June. And he would begin his prison term on October 27 if his
appeal was rejected.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Labor party welcomed the sentence, saying in a
statement that it is important three years after Rabin's
assassination to see the justice has been done for the
perpetrators, accomplices and those who failed to prevent the
crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
