<DOCNO> XIE19980927.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: A Special Visit to Pioneers of Rural Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- On the eve of the 20th
anniversary of China's reforms, President Jiang Zemin paid a
special visit to Xiaogang, a small village in Anhui Province and a
pace-setter of the country's rural reform.
</P>
<P>
One cold night 20 years ago, 18 farmers in Xiaogang signed an
agreement to contract the then collectively owned farmland. The
practice later developed into the renowned "household contract
responsibility system with remuneration linked to output" carried
out in rural areas throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
On September 22, the president walked into the village's
exhibition room filled with pictures showing the great changes in
Xiaogang in the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Yan Junchang, leader of the village in 1978, told the president
that in 1979, the second year after they instituted the contract
system, the village had a grain output of 65,000 kilograms, equal
the total in the 15 years from 1955 to 1970.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed pleasures over the marvelous achievements the
villagers have made, praising the farmer's ability to use very
simple words to state clearly the benefits of the contract system.
</P>
<P>
After visiting the village's library and the farmers' school of
technology, the president talked with farmers in one of their
homes.
</P>
<P>
"This is my first visit to the village, but I have always been
concerned about its development because Deng Xiaoping's policy of
reforms and opening up first bore fruits in the rural areas, and
Xiaogang was the first," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the household contract responsibility system
would not change. The contract system will last for another 30
years, and it need not change after that, he said.
</P>
<P>
Villagers were impressed by the president's talk and responded
with warm applause during his speech.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the central government has paid close attention to
agriculture and rural issues. The reforms in rural areas should
continue to be carried out and productivity in rural areas should
be further developed, he said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to step up research for drawing up
China's agricultural development strategy for the coming century
to promote long-term, steady development of agriculture, Jiang
told the farmers.
</P>
<P>
"This work is of great significance and that is why I came here
to see for myself," the president said. "I just want to
learn from all of you."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
