<HEADLINE> Jewish Settler Banned From Entering Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Jerusalem Magistrate Court
on Sunday banned Jewish settler Avshalom Ladani from entering the
Palestinian territories for his alleged killing of a Palestinian
student last week.
</P>
<P>
The Court also ordered the Israeli police to submit on Monday
the investigation report about the incident and then the Court
will decide what legal actions can be taken against Ladani.
</P>
<P>
Ladani, 35 and from Dolev Settlement in the West Bank, opened
fire to a group of Palestinian students on September 17 near the
West Bank city of Ramallah. One Palestinian student was killed
and another injured in the incident.
</P>
<P>
Ladani surrendered to Jerusalem police that evening and
admitted that he had opened fire toward the Palestinian
students.
</P>
<P>
He also told the police that other settlers in his car, which
was stoned by the students, also opened fire toward the students
and he was not sure that the student was killed by his shooting.
</P>
<P>
Ladani was remanded by the Court on September 18 and two days
later was released and put under "house arrest" in a Jerusalem
hostel pending further charges.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem police said Sunday that the investigation is still
going on and the police has yet to determine if Ladani was the
killer or he fired in self-defense.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian side strongly condemned the shooting and
demanded that Ladani be turned over to the Palestinian court for
trial. 
</P>
