months for mistakes committed by the country's gendarmerie.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian cabinet met on Friday to discuss the resignation
letter handed in by Tobback following the death of 20-year-old
Semira Adamu but decided to give him 24 hours to ponder over his
decision.
</P>
<P>
Adamu died of brain hemorrhage on Tuesday in a local
hospital. The Nigerian woman became unconscious after the two
gendarmes escorting her to a Nigeria-bound flight used a cushion
to muffle her screams.
</P>
<P>
An investigation was launched into the death of Adamu and one
of the two gendarmes involved in Tuesday's incident had been found
to have been disciplined in a similar case previously.
</P>
<P>
Two other refugees died from suffocation in the process of
expulsion in Belgium in 1982 and 1987 respectively, local press
reports claimed.
</P>
<P>
In April this year, Tobback's predecessor resigned after
Belgium's notorious child rapist and killer Marc Dutroux
overwhelmed two escorting gendarmes and escaped from a pre-trial
hearing.
</P>
