now is the sixth largest international traveler destiny in the
world.
</P>
<P>
In order to promote the Chinese economy, the country has
lowered its tariffs on five occasions since 1992, with average
tariff rate dropped to 17 percent from 43.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
China has also stopped subsidizing its foreign trade companies
and adopted a unified, controlled floating exchange rate of its
currency.
</P>
<P>
It has drafted and put into force laws and regulations on
foreign trade, imports, exports, anti-dumping and anti-subsidy
issues.
</P>
<P>
China now has 160,000 companies to conduct foreign trade and do
related businesses, which enjoy the same income tax rates as other
enterprises do.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign trade and attraction of foreign investment have
maintained a sound momentum. In the past two decades, foreign
investment has gone beyond the scope of manufacturing and
construction industries to enter all principal sectors of the
economy, including agriculture, industry, transport and
telecommunications, commercial retail, catering and entertainment,
finance and insurance.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment now supports 0.5 percent of agriculture, 3.7
percent of transport and telecommunications and 3.1 percent of
retail industry in China.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the mix of export commodities has keep
improving. Manufactured goods now account for 86.9 percent of the
total exports value, as against merely 46.5 percent 20 years
ago. And machinery and electronic products has replaced textiles
as the largest export commodity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
