<HEADLINE> Southwest China Iron, Steel Base Absorbs More Investment (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ertan Hydropower Plant,
expected to be China's largest power plant built in the 20th
century, has gone into commercial operation.
</P>
<P>
However, the plant takes advantage of less than one third of
the hydropower resources of the Panzhihua-Xichang Region in
southwestern Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Covering an area of 67,000 sq km and taking Panzhihua and
Xichang as its central cities, the Panzhihua-Xichang region has
become a new hot spot for domestic and overseas investment because
of its abundant natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Apart from its water resources, which are the richest in the
country, the region also abounds in deposits of iron, vanadium and
titanium, which account for 13, 69 and 93 percent, respectively,
of the country's totals.
</P>
<P>
According to Xie Hong, director of the office in charge of the
exploitation of local natural resources, more than 260 Chinese and
foreign investors have so far poured approximately two billion
U.S. dollars into the region since 1990, with another 50 or 60
billion yuan (6.04 billion to 7.25 billion US dollars) from
governments at different levels.
</P>
<P>
In the mid-1960s, large-scale exploration work started in the
southwest region to turn Panzhihua into western China's largest
iron and steel industrial base and Xichang into a satellite
launching center.
</P>
<P>
The area has witnessed not only rapid progress in
infrastructure construction, but also high returns on various
types of investment, according to Sun Honglie, a noted economist
as well as an academician with the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980927.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China Iron, Steel Base Absorbs More Investment (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sun said the ratio of investment and corresponding pre-tax
profit in the region was 1 to 0.7 in the 25 years from 1965 to
1990, 1.5 times higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, an international banking group comprising 24 foreign
banks from the United States, Japan, Britain and other countries
and regions reaped some 86 million U.S. dollars-worth of profit
from their 200-million-U.S.dollar syndicated loans, which further
boosted investors' confidence.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the central government promised an annual input of
more than 30 million yuan (3.6 million US dollars), beginning in
1996, into the region to boost the exploration of natural
resources.
</P>
<P>
Aside from the Ertan Hydropower Plant, which has already drawn
1.2 billion U.S. dollars-worth of investment from the World Bank,
four other such hydroelectic power plants at state-level are
expected to start construction soon, with a combined capacity of
25.5 million kw.
</P>
<P>
All these are part of China's effort to narrow the disparities
between the coastal area and central-western region, which will
provide the Panzhihua-Xichang Region with great opportunities for
development, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the century, these key projects in the region
completed or scheduled in near future will create a huge market
demand, and thus provide more ideal opportunities for business
people from both at home and abroad, Sun predicted. 
