<HEADLINE> Lewis Beats Mavrovic to WBC Heavyweight Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WAHINGTON, September 26 (Xinhua) -- WBC heavyweight champion
Lennox Lewis of Britain couldn't knock out his challenger Zeljko
Mavrovic of Croatia but won a 12-round unanimous decision in a
fight at the Uncasville, Connecticut, the United States, on Satu
rday night.
</P>
<P>
There were no knockdowns, although Lewis was cut in the mouth
and Mavrovic was hit badly on his both eyes.
</P>
<P>
Judge Franfisco Ciminale of Italy scored it 117-111, Tommy
Kaczmarak of New Jersy had it 119-109, and Bob Logist of Begium
scored it 117-112.
</P>
<P>
Lewis controlled the bout with hard right uppercuts and stiff
left. "I said before the fight 'You are my friend' and I meant
'You are my friend," Mavrovic said in the ring. "You beat me, and
nobody ever beat me before."
</P>
<P>
Mavrovic entered the fight 27-0 with 22 knockouts. Lewis
improved his record to 34-1 with 27 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
"Mavrovic must have 240 pounds of steel in his chin," said
Frank Maloney, Lewis' manager.
</P>
<P>
Lewis said:"I trained wrong. I was expecting him to run. I was
pleased with myself I showed I can adjust in the ring."
</P>
<P>
Mavrovic, the European heavyweight champion, landed 132 of 298
punches, while Lewis hit 216 of 507 punches in this mandatory WBC
heavyweight defense. 
