<HEADLINE> Seles Wins Third Successive Princess Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one Monica
Seles of the United States beat Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario of Spain
to capture her third straight Princess Cup tennis championship
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Seles surged after losing the first set to take the match 4-6,
6-3, 6-4 in two hours 17 minutes, beating Sanchez Vicario in the
event for the third straight year.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez-Vicario came back from a 3-1 deficit to win the first
set, and threatened to rebound from 3-1 and 5-3 gaps in the
third. But at 30-all in the final game, Seles stopped her strong
rally with two good serves.
</P>
<P>
Seles, seeded second here behind the French Open champion,
saved two break points in the second game and two more in the
fourth en route to winning the final set.
</P>
<P>
She now has won 17 of their 20 meetings.
</P>
<P>
The two were to meet again later Sunday in the doubles final.
Seles was playing with 17-year-old Russian Anna Kournikova, and
Sanchez-Vicario with American Mary Joe Fernandez. 
</P>
