tennis tournament Saturday in Milwaukee, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Italians Diego Nargiso and Andrea Gaudenzi beat Justin
Gimelstob and Tobb Martin 6-4, 7-6 (7-3), 5-7, 2-6, 6-3 to
eliminate the U.S.team in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Italy will play Sweden in the finals on December 4.
</P>
<P>
"It's an unbelievable feeling. I never felt anything like this
before," Nargiso said.
</P>
<P>
The United States' defeat snaped its winning streak of 18 home
Davis Cup matches. They last lost in the United States in 1987.
</P>
<P>
"It's something I never dreamed of and neither did our
players," U.S. captain Tom Gullikson said.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, Guadenzi beat Jan-Michael and David Sanguinetti
upset Martin in the opening singles matches.
</P>
<P>
Italy lost won the Davis Cup in 1976. It entered the
semi-final round last year, but was beaten by Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Peter Sampras, Andre Agassi and Michael Chang skipped the
tournament, Jim Courier did not play because of an injured arm.
