<HEADLINE> Over 0.4 Mln People Affected by Water-Borne Diseases in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Diarrhea and other water-borne
diseases have so far attacked over 400,000 people in flood-hit
Bangladesh, of whom 523 died, The New Nation daily reported
Sunday, quoting official sources.
</P>
<P>
However, unofficial estimates suggest that the number of
affected people and that of dead due to diarrhea will be much
higher, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from diarrhea, the spread of malaria, jaundice and
various skin diseases is also being reported from far-flung areas
of the country.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 government medical teams are now working in the
flood-affected areas to treat the infected people, and various
voluntary organizations and non-government organizations are also
rendering medical services in the areas.
</P>
<P>
However, with the recession of flood waters, the number of
people afflicted by the water-borne diseases is rising every day,
the report observed. 
</P>
