<HEADLINE> EU Finance Ministers End Meeting in Vienna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- European Union finance ministers
discussed the Russian financial crisis, world economy and internal
problems at a two-day meeting here, Austrian Finance Minister
Rudolf Edlniger who acted as chairman of the meeting said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Finance ministers and central bank governors of 15 EU members
agreed that resolution of the economic and financial crisis in
Russia, Japan and other Asian countries would depend on the
political and economic situation there, Edlniger told reporters at
the end of the meeting Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The EU could not offer any cash money to Russia, but would aid
it under an assistance plan started by the EU since 1991, he said.
</P>
<P>
President of the European commission Jacques Santer said at the
joint news conference that any aid to Russia would be given to
"help Russia save itself."
</P>
<P>
The finance chiefs could not agree however on how the euro-zone
should be represented in international financial bodies such as
the IMF and the Group-7. But an agreement is expected before the
first day of December.
</P>
<P>
EU finance Commissioner Yves-Thibault de Silguy, Managing
Director of the International Monetary Fund Michel Camdessus and
the President of the European Central Bank were also present at
the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
