<HEADLINE> Scenic Area on West Lake to Be Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The city of Hangzhou, a
popular tourist destination in east China, will expand the Lingyin
scenic area along the western side of the city's West Lake,
according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The Lingyin scenic area, a key part of the picturesque West
Lake Scenic Region, consists of Feilai Hilltop, Lingyin Temple and
Tianzhu Temple and has an area of 16.73 hectares. This spot
receives about four million tourists annually.
</P>
<P>
Through this expansion, eight new scenic sites will be added to
the Lingyin area, enlarging it to 226.7 hectares, and the expanded
Lingyin Temple will highlight Buddhist culture.
</P>
<P>
The expansion will be carried out in two stages, and the first
phase of construction will be completed in the year 2000. A tunnel
from Tianzhu to Meijiawu will also be built to connect the Lingyin
scenic area to other scenic spots in and around the West Lake
Scenic Region such as Jiuxiyanshu village and the Liuhe Pagoda,
sources said.  
</P>
