<HEADLINE> Hurricane Georges Approaches Mexican Gulf Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Hurricane Georges
increased its speed and force and is moving into the east of the
Gulf of Mexico, the Mexican National Meteorological Service
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The phenomenon presents top sustained winds of 100 mph and
squalls of 128 mph.
</P>
<P>
Georges will get stronger Saturday night, bringing heavy rains
and hurricane force winds over the west of Cuba and south of
Florida in the United States, said the meteorological service.
</P>
<P>
The hurricane is causing low pressure on the coasts of
Tamaulipas and Veracruz, resulting in storms in the south of the
country and rains in the center of Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The hurricane has killed about 300 people so far in the
Dominican Republic, Haiti, Cuba and Puerto Rico. 
