<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- China's fixed assets
investment plan will result in great opportunities for the Swiss
Reinsurance Group (Swiss Re), today's China Daily quotes the
company's chief executive officer Waler B. Kielholz as saying.
</P>
<P>
The investment will create demand for huge amounts of machinery
and equipment, which will need to be insured.
</P>
<P>
"But the insurance market in China is not in a position to
cover all these demands," he said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Chinese insurance companies will seek financial
support from the world reinsurance market to ensure economic
stability.
</P>
<P>
Company chairman Ulrich Bremi said Swiss Re has been
paying great attention to its development in the China market.
</P>
<P>
To show its confidence and commitment to China, Swiss Re last
week held a group executive meeting in Shanghai attended by 120
senior officials.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time Swiss Re had held such a meeting
outside Europe since its founding in 1863.
</P>
<P>
Bremi said the meeting in Shanghai was aimed to let senior
officials better understand the changes and potential in China,
which will have a huge influence on the company's strategy.
</P>
<P>
"Our commitment in China is for the long term and will not be
influenced by the regional financial crisis," he said.  
