worth over 14 billion baht (364 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The manufacturers should have no problem with the cancellation
and should refund the deposit because the TAI is a good customer,
he said, adding that if the manufacturers proceed with the
construction and the airways refuses to buy, it will be difficult
to find another customer for the aircraft designed for TAI.
</P>
<P>
The national airline has placed a deposit of 148 million
dollars for the aircraft and is required to pay another 216
million dollars to complete the deal.
</P>
<P>
Smith said his committee would forward its proposal to
Transport and Communications Minister Suthep Thueksuban next
Monday for approval.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was in line with the ministry's policy to have
TAI's aircraft procurement plan reviewed to save national
expenses, Smith said.
</P>
<P>
If Boeing and Airbus rejected the proposal, TAI should
negotiate for changing aircraft types or for extending the
schedule for their delivery, Smith said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, TAI was making another negotiation with Airbus
Industrie to change a purchase contract for five Airbus 300-600s
into an 11-year lease deal, Smith said.
</P>
<P>
The five aircraft were already completed but TAI had yet to
find a budget to pay for their delivery, according to Smith.
</P>
<P>
TAI has already paid 9 million dollars in fine plus interest
for having the delivery delayed.
</P>
<P>
Smith said TAI should buy the five aircraft if it could raise
enough money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
