<HEADLINE> Equities Overcome Initial Sluggishness on BSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Equities overcame initial
hesitancy after receiving gradual and good support mid-week
onwards and moved widely in brisk activity on the Bombay Stock
Exchange (BSE) market during the week.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index spurted by 132.85 points to end the
week at 3223.57 as against last weekend's close of 3090.72. The
national index gained 52.50 points to 1424.72 at the weekend from
the previous close of 1372.22. The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index
were quoted sharply up at 329.28 and 128.96 at the weekend
compared with last weekend close of 317.37 and 124.24
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Operators attributed the rising equities to the agreement
reached by Indo-Pak prime ministers in New York on September 23 to
resume the two countries' dialogue from next month as well as a
sharp upsurge in Wall Street and U.K. stock which have boosted the
sentiment on Southeast Asian markets. 
</P>
