<HEADLINE> Banks Punished for Illegal Deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Five banks in Guangdong
Province were deprived of the right to run foreign exchange
business or had their right to sell foreign exchange suspended for
six months to a year recently, says today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
These five banks are Zengcheng Sub-Branch of the Guangdong
Development Bank, Jiangmen Branch of the China Construction Bank,
Nanhai Sub-Branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China,
Jiangmen Branch of the China Agricultural Bank and Zhuhai Branch
of the Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
Their illegal activities were listed as: conducting foreign
exchange business beyond their approved scope; concealing foreign
exchange sales; selling and paying foreign exchange on invalid
declaration forms; selling foreign exchange to those without
complete documents and certificates, and so on.
</P>
<P>
To prevent cheating in buying foreign exchange and to plug
sources of underground foreign exchange business, the Guangdong
Branch of the State Administration of Foreign Exchange (Safe)
recently promulgated eight measures to strengthen management.
</P>
<P>
</P>
