<HEADLINE> Bolivia to Auction Away Telecommunications Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LA PAZ, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Bolivian government will
auction all its telecommunications services next year, a Bolivian
official said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Jose Alfredo Arce, director of communications in the Economic
Development Ministry, said Saturday that a plan to open the
telecommunications market is being drafted for the bidding, which
is expected to be completed in the next six months.
</P>
<P>
Although the monopoly of the telecommunications will end on
November 27, 2001, the telecommunications law stipulates that the
services can be auctioned in advance and the new owners will start
operating on November 28, 2001, Arce said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the telecommunications services include satellite
television, digital radio, video conferences and mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
Vice President of TELECEL Juan Pablo Calvo said the bidding
can improve services and benefit customers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
