<HEADLINE> Brazil Increases Exports to Arab Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian exports to
Arab countries rose by 14.51 percent in the first half of this
year, compared with the same period last year, the Arab-Brazilian
Chamber of Commerce said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The chamber said that Brazilian exports to 20 Arab countries
amounted to 782.9 million U.S. dollars in January-June, 99 million
dollars more than that in the first six months of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Jordan registered the biggest increase in imports from Brazil
from 15.8 million dollars last year to 82.6 million dollars this
year, followed by Egypt from 75.8 million dollars to 125 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
