<HEADLINE> Ashley Wins Vacant European Boxing Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- British and Commonwealth
champion Crawford Ashley took the vacant European
light-heavyweight title on a split decision against previously
unbeaten Joe Siluvangi of France in York late Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ashley had a 116-112 margin on the scorecard of Danish judge
Freddy Christensen, while Hungarian Bela Florian scored it
116-114 in favour of the English boxer.
</P>
<P>
Luxembourg official Tonio Tiberi, however, had a narrow
116-115 verdict for the Frenchman. 
</P>
