<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hide Retains WBO Heavyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Herbie Hide
retained his World Boxing Organisation (WBO) heavyweight title in
Norwich, England, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The referee, Joe Cortez, stepped in to stop Hide's defence
against Willi Fischer in the second round of a scheduled
twelve-round contest after a flurry of explosive punches had
floored the German challenger three times.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old British fighter took charge from the start and
Fischer could not cope with Hide's power and speed.
</P>
<P>
He first fell early in the second round to a big left, and
after going down again for a mandatory eight count, the final
result was never in doubt. When another punishing left from Hide
sent Fischer crashing back to the canvas the referee wisely
called a halt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
