<HEADLINE> Construction to Start on Guangzhou's New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The work of construction
will start on a new airport in this capital of south China's
Guangdong Province at the end of this year, according to local
sources.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project is expected to be completed and
go into operation by the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
The new airport, covering an area of 1,444 ha, is 28 km from
the center of Guangzhou and 17 km from the old airport.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that this project will cost 18.94 billion yuan
(about 2.29 billion US dollars), and after its completion it will
be capable of accommodating the largest planes in the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
