<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sweden Advances to Davis Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Sweden
overwhelmed Spain 3-0 in the World Group semi-finals to advance
to the Davis Cup final on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
After winning two tough opening singles, Swedish pair Jonas
Bjorkman and Nicklas Kulti defeated Spain's Javier Sanchez and
Julian Alonswon in three straight sets, 6-2, 6-2, 6-2 at the
Royal Tennis Hall here.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's lopsided win gave Sweden an unbeatable 3-0
advantage in the best-of-five match semi-final.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman gave Sweden a 1-0 lead on Friday with a 6-3, 7-5, 6-7
(5-7), 6-3 victory over Alex Corretja.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Thomas Johansson had a dream debut in the second
singles match, edging Carlos Moya of Spain 7-5, 7-6 (7-4), 7-6
(8-6).
</P>
<P>
Sunday's reverse singles are likely to be shortened to
best-of-3 sets. Bjorkman is scheduled to start against Moya in a
match between the team's No. 1 selections.
</P>
<P>
Sweden has played 11 finals since its first victory at the
Royal Tennis Hall in 1975, when former great Bjorn Borg anchored
the team. With its six wins and five runners-up finishes, Sweden
is the most successful Davis Cup nation in the last two decades.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
