<HEADLINE> Lloyd Retains British Bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Paul Lloyd retained his
British and Commonwealth bantamweight titles in York on Saturday
by outpointing Scotland's Drew Docherty over twelve rounds.
</P>
<P>
Lloyd wanted to erase the memory of his humiliating two round
IBF defeat against Tim Austin in March.
</P>
<P>
Docherty was fighting for the first time in 18 months
following his European title defeat to Denmark's Johnny Bredahl.
</P>
<P>
It was Lloyd's 18th win in 23 fights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
