<HEADLINE> Villa Win Top Clash but Sending-off Dominates Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Aston Villa won the English
premier league's top-of-the-table clash with a 1-0 win over Derby
County on Saturday but the day's action was dominated by one of
the most spectacular sending-offs in Britain for years.
</P>
<P>
Sheffield Wednesday's Italian striker Paolo di Canio floored
referee Paul Alcock seconds after being shown the red card for
violent conduct in his team's 1-0 victory over reigning champions
Arsenal.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal's Martin Keown was also sent off after the mass brawl
on the pitch. But di Canio's aggressive shove on Alcock is likely
to end in a tough sanction from English soccer authorities and
dominate the headlines.
</P>
<P>
England international Paul Merson, a recent signing from
Middlesbrough, helped Villa stay on top of the table with a
well-taken 15th minute goal in the crucial Midlands derby at
Villa Park.
</P>
<P>
After beating the Derby offside trap, Merson sprinted down the
middle of the pitch and slotted the ball just inside the
left-hand post. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
